Business Brief -- Child World Inc.:
   Bankers Permit Suspension
   Of Payment on Credit Line
Child World said it signed a preliminary agreement with
Foothill Capital Corp. for a $25 million reserve facility,
subject to various conditions including the consent of the
bank group. The facility would be in addition to the
company's normal revolving line of credit.
   Meanwhile, Child World said it received letters of
interest from several potential equity partners regarding an
additional infusion of capital. Earlier, Child World said
that if an equity investment is made, "it would be for a
large stake in the company for a large amount of money."